definition.value: A gluconate that is the conjugate base of lactobionic acid arising from the deprotonation of the carboxy group.
Major species at pH 7.3.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of 3-(4-aminophenyl)pyruvic acid. Major species at pH 7.3.
An amino acid zwitterion arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of 4-amino-L-phenylalanine; major species at pH 7.3.
Major species at pH 7.3.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as dichloroacetyl; major species at pH 7.3.
A zwitterion arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of L-homocarnosine; major species at pH 7.3.
A L-histidine derivative that is L-histidine substituted by a methyl group at position 3 on the imidazole ring; major species at pH 7.3.
A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is 3-(4-aminophenyl)propanoic acid which is substituted by an oxo group at position 2.
A phenylalanine derivative that is phenylalanine carrying an amino group at position 4 on the benzene ring.
A D-alpha-amino acid zwitterion arising from the transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of D-leucine; major species at pH 7.3.
A D-alpha-amino acid zwitterion arising from the transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of D-norleucine; major species at pH 7.3.
A D-alpha-amino acid zwitterion arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of D-homoserine; major species at pH 7.3.
A mycocerosic acid is a methyl-branched fatty acid with 24 to 35 carbon atoms. From 2 to 5 conjugated methyl groups are attached, starting at the 2-position.
The D-enantiomer of 4-aminophenylalanine.
A compound having bonds between one or more metalloid atoms and one or more carbon atoms of an organyl group.
A phthiocerol dimycocerosate (DIM) is a phthiocerol based lipid where the two hydroxyl groups are esterified with a mycocerosic acid (ChEBI:143082).
A 4-hydroxynon-2-enoic acid in which the double bond has (E)-configuration.
A hydroxy saturated fatty acid anion resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of 10-hydroxyoctadecanoic acid.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 2'-3'-cGAMP; major species at pH 7.3.
